    <main>

          <!-- Toggle sections -->
          <section class="faq-section">
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-header">
                    <p class="faq-question">What should I bring?</p>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>You do not have to bring anything to your treatment except for <strong>"you"</strong>.</p>
                    <p>No matter how hectic your day is or where you are coming from...</p>
                    <p>We have robes available for you to change and unwind into if needed.</p>
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-header">
                    <p class="faq-question">What should I leave at home?</p>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p><strong>Loud Voices: </strong> Meraki is a place of sanctuary and relaxation from the outside world where you can enjoy some much needed quiet time. We ask that you please be respectful of other guests who may be seeking quiet solitude and keep you voices down.</p>

                    <p><strong>Heavy Scents: </strong> Please do not wear any heavy perfume, cologne, body spray, etc... while visiting Meraki. </p>
                    
                        <p><strong>Valuables: </strong> Please leave your valuables at home as we are not responsible for lost or stolen items. </p>
                </div>
            </div>



            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-header">
                    <p class="faq-question">What if I’m late for an appointment?</p>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>We understand that sometimes life happens and you may run a few minutes behind...</p>
                    <p>We will try our best to accommodate your full session, however based on availability and limited time allowances in between bookings we may need to shorten your session.</p>
                </div>
            </div>




            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-header">
                    <p class="faq-question">What are your cancellation policies?</p>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Please give us a call at <strong>604-383-0123</strong>, to reschedule or cancel your appointment by phone during our business hours with<strong> 24 hours notice</strong>.</p>
                    <p><strong>If you cancel your appointment or "no show" with less than 24 hours notice, we reserve the right to charge your credit card for the full amount of your appointment.</p></strong>                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-header">
                    <p class="faq-question">Where do I find parking?</p>
                    <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    <p>Free parking is conveniently available in front of Meraki Therapeutics and surrounding areas within the Tsawwassen Commons.</p>
                </div>            
            </div>
        </section>
        





    </main>

    <script>
        // Select the hamburger menu and nav
        const hamburger = document.getElementById('hamburger-menu');
        const nav = document.querySelector('nav');
    
        // Toggle the nav visibility when the hamburger icon is clicked
        hamburger.addEventListener('click', function() {
            nav.classList.toggle('active');
        });
    </script>


<script>
document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(item => {
    const toggle = item.querySelector('.faq-toggle');
    const answer = item.querySelector('.faq-answer');
    const header = item.querySelector('.faq-header');

    header.addEventListener('click', function() {
        // Toggle active state
        item.classList.toggle('active');

        // Toggle answer display and icon
        if (item.classList.contains('active')) {
            answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px'; // Expand to content height
            toggle.textContent = '-'; // Change to minus when active
        } else {
            answer.style.maxHeight = null; // Collapse back
            toggle.textContent = '+'; // Change back to plus when inactive
        }
    });
});

    
</script>
    
    
